\begin_layout Subsubsection
Drought factor
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Drought Factor (DF) equation and calculation procedures were developed
 by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Griffiths1999"

\end_inset

, which corresponds to an improved formula originally proposed by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Noble1980"

\end_inset

.
 The DF ranges form 1 to 10 and the value depends on the number of days
 of the last significant rain and soil dryness.
 According to the author, the procedure to identify the last significant
 rain consists in analyzing 20 consecutive days and assigning to the day
 of the highest rain the sum of the rain of the whole range.
 The soil dryness represents the amount of rain necessary to saturate the
 upper 200 mm of soil layer, and is determined as an index usually calculated
 by the methodologies proposed by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "KeetchJJ"

\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Mount1972"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

