\begin_layout Subsection
Seasonal forescasting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seasonal forecasting uses statistical-empirical methods as well as dynamical
 models 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013,Troccoli2005"

\end_inset

.
 Statistical- empirical models describe the relationship between predictands
 and predictors usually assuming linear relationships.
 Common predictans are temperature and precipitation 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013,Pepler2015,Troccoli2005"

\end_inset

.
 Usual predictors are sea surface temperature, soil moisture, snow cover
 and sea ice 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013,Troccoli2005"

\end_inset

.
 One of the most common problems with this approach is multicollinearity
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Troccoli2005"

\end_inset

.
 This occurs when several predictors are variables in the forecast and they
 are correlated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dynamical forecasts rely on the physical modelation of the climate system.
 A simple model describes the interactions of the atmosphere only.
 In complex models, all the components of the system and their interactions
 take part.
 Setting initial conditions and insufficient knowledge of physical processes
 are common problems with them 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013,Troccoli2005"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dynamical models have in general better forecasting accuracy than statistical-em
pirical methods
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013"

\end_inset

.
 Additionally, ensemble dynamical models perform better than a single model
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Pepler2015"

\end_inset

.
 Yet, sophisticated statistical methods can have an accuracy comparable
 to the dynamical counterparts
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013"

\end_inset

.
 In practise, decision-makers use a combination of statistical-empirical
 and dynamical approaches 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Doblas-Reyes2013"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
